  "prompt": "Is Xiaomi Redmi Note 3 up gradable to Marshmallow?",
  "response": "Yes, the Xiaomi Redmi Note 3 can be upgraded to Android 6.0 Marshmallow. When the device was initially released in 2015, it typically came with Android 5.3 Lollipop customized with Xiaomi's MIUI interface. Xiaomi provided official updates that allowed Redmi Note 3 users to upgrade their devices to Android Marshmallow.\n\n**Here's how you can check and perform the upgrade:**\n\n1. **Check for Official Updates:**\n   - **Navigate to Settings:** Open the **Settings** app on your Redmi Note 3.\n   - **About Phone:** Scroll down and tap on **\"About phone.\"**\n   - **System Update:** Tap on **\"System update\"** to check if the update to Marshmallow (or a newer version) is available for your device.\n   - **Download and Install:** If the update is available, follow the on-screen instructions to download and install it.\n\n2. **Using MIUI Update Tool:**\n   - Download and install the official **Mi Flash Tool** or use the **MIUI Update** tool available in the device\u2019s settings.\n   - Ensure your device is connected to a stable Wi-Fi network and has sufficient battery before starting the update process.\n\n3. **Custom ROMs (Advanced Users):**\n   - If the official update is no longer available or you want a newer version of Android, you might consider installing a custom ROM like **LineageOS** or other community-supported ROMs.\n   - **Caution:** Installing custom ROMs can void your warranty and carries risks like bricking your device. Ensure you follow detailed guides and understand the process before proceeding.\n\n**Additional Tips:**\n\n- **Backup Your Data:** Before performing any system updates, it's crucial to back up your important data to avoid potential data loss.\n  \n- **Check Compatibility:** Ensure that the update is compatible with your specific model and region, as firmware can vary.\n\n- **Storage Space:** Make sure you have enough storage space available on your device to download and install the update.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to successfully upgrade your Xiaomi Redmi Note 3 to Android Marshmallow, enhancing its performance and accessing new features.",
